{#def layout="block", padding="default", interactive=False, tag="div", href="", extra="" #}
{#
  Card surface with a configurable inner layout. The visual shell (white
  background, zinc-200 border, rounded corners) is the shared
  ``.minds-card`` CSS class in static/app.css so JS-rendered cards
  (e.g. the providers list in pages/Landing.jinja) can reference the same
  surface without copy-pasting the Tailwind utility string. ``.minds-card``
  has no baseline shadow -- non-clickable cards read as flat surfaces; the
  ``interactive`` prop adds ``hover:shadow-raised`` so clickable cards lift on
  hover.

  Props:
    layout      "block" (default), "row", or "row-spread".
                  - block:      no flex; caller arranges children.
                  - row:        flex items-center gap-1.5 (children flow left-to-right;
                                a flex-1 child pushes following items to the right edge).
                  - row-spread: flex items-center justify-between gap-1.5 (header/action layout).
    padding     "default" (p-4) or "tight" (px-4 py-2).
    interactive Adds cursor-pointer + hover:border-strong so the
                surface reads as clickable. Typical with tag="a".
    tag         "div" (default), "a", or "button". Use "a" for click-anywhere
                navigation; pass href=... when "a".
    href        href for tag="a".
    extra       Trailing Tailwind for one-off overrides (e.g. "mt-4", "accent-spine").

  Any HTML attribute on the tag that is not declared above (style=, data-*,
  onclick=, id=, title=, aria-*) flows through via JinjaX's ``attrs``
  passthrough -- callers don't have to enumerate them here.

  Usage:
    <Card>basic block card</Card>
    <Card layout="row-spread"><span>name</span><Button>Action</Button></Card>
    <Card tag="a" href="/x" layout="row" interactive padding="tight" extra="accent-spine">
      ...
    </Card>
#}
{%- set _layout_cls = {
  "block": "",
  "row": "flex items-center gap-1.5",
  "row-spread": "flex items-center justify-between gap-1.5",
}[layout] -%}
{%- set _padding_cls = {
  "default": "p-4",
  "tight": "px-4 py-2",
}[padding] -%}
{%- set _interactive_cls = "cursor-pointer hover:border-strong hover:shadow-raised" if interactive else "" -%}
{%- set _anchor_cls = "no-underline text-inherit" if tag == "a" else "" -%}
{%- set _cls = ["minds-card", _layout_cls, _padding_cls, _interactive_cls, _anchor_cls, extra] | reject("equalto", "") | join(" ") -%}
{%- if tag == "a" -%}
<a {{ attrs.render(classes=_cls, href=href) }}>{{ content }}</a>
{%- elif tag == "button" -%}
<button {{ attrs.render(classes=_cls, type="button") }}>{{ content }}</button>
{%- else -%}
<div {{ attrs.render(classes=_cls) }}>{{ content }}</div>
{%- endif -%}
